We need to prove that for $n \geq 4$, any sequence of calls that makes all $n$ agents experts must have length at least $2n - 4$.

First, let's think about the problem structure. We have $n$ agents, and each call connects two agents. After a call, both agents know the secrets of each other. We need to show that to make all $n$ agents experts (i.e., all know the initial secret of every other agent), we need at least $2n - 4$ calls.

The proof strategy is by contradiction. Assume that there exists a sequence of calls of length less than $2n - 4$ that makes all agents experts. Then, we derive a contradiction.

