  -- Let's use the fact that all n experts are in the sequence.
  -- From exp_needs_n_min_one_calls, for each k, n-1 < σ.length.
  -- Total calls needed would be at least n*(n-1).
  -- But σ has length ≤ 2*n - 5.
  -- So n*(n-1) ≤ 2*n - 5.
  -- This is n² - n ≤ 2n - 5, i.e., n² - 3n + 5 ≤ 0.
  -- The roots of n² - 3n + 5 = 0 are complex, meaning the quadratic is always positive.
  -- So n² - 3n + 5 > 0 for all real (and natural) n.
